*Evidence:*
- Reduced readmissions
- Fewer adverse drug events
- Increased caregiver satisfaction
- Better self-care confidence

## Systematic Resource Navigation

**Care Transitions Intervention (CTI)**

*Evidence-Based Model:*
- Rooted in Coleman's work
- Coach works with caregiver during transition
- Tools: medication list, red flags, personal health record
- Follow-up support

*Outcomes:*
- 30-50% reduction in readmissions
- Reduced medication errors
- Increased caregiver preparedness

**GRACE (Geriatric Resources for Assessment and Care of Elders)**

*Team-Based Model:*
- Interdisciplinary team (NP, social worker, geriatrician, pharmacist)
- In-home comprehensive assessment
- Caregiver included as team member
- Ongoing care coordination and follow-up

*Outcomes:*
- Improved quality of care
- Reduced emergency department use
- Better caregiver outcomes
- Cost-effective

